description:
Brian Azzarello and Lee Bermejo, the same writer/artist team behind &quot;Joker&quot; (2008), work together here in an earlier story that features a Batman crossover with the Wildstorm imprint's Deathblow. Promotional info from the collected edition - &quot;One is the World's Greatest Detective with unlimited resources for his vigilante quest for justice. The other is a soldier; a blackops killer who does whatever it takes for the greater good. What happens when the two meet? We'll never know because Michael Cray, code-name Deathblow, is dead. The Dark Knight faces the daunting task of finishing a job that someone else started but
for reasons that remain a mystery, refused to finish. That someone was Michael Cray.&quot;

Previously there were digital releases of this miniseries by Son of Ultron-Empire; however these Minutmen-PhD versions are of similar resolution and take up a little less space on your hard drive. Both are now torrented so the choice is up to you. Thanks to all the scanner groups for their efforts; please seed and enjoy! :-)
